<h4>What is GitHub?</h4>
<p>
    <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> is a collaborative platform that allows professionals to work in teams and utilize a process known
    as Source Control or Version Control. Source control allows developers to keep track of all changes that have been made to our files,
    work on features simultaneously, fix bugs and roll out patches quickly, and work in teams effectively. As we get more advanced we can
    take advantage of GitHub features like automation and security to make us more productive and roll out fixes and features
    faster than our competition.
</p>
<h4>What is Microsoft Azure?</h4>
<p>
    We use Microsoft's cloud platform Azure to get some experience with cloud platforms and some technologies they offer.
    Utilizing free student credits, students host their portfolio applications in the cloud.
</p>